 innate differences are important, without necessarily having prejudice or discrimination, but this is rare; it's theoretically possible, but it's pretty rare, I think, to have a purely intellectual belief in race without being a racist. Race is a set of beliefs without necessarily either the prejudice or the discrimination; just the intellectual belief that there are innate differences between people that don't necessarily translate into inequality. I think some people use the word \"racialism\" for that kind of belief which is, as I say, pretty rare, but it's possible.</p>"},"field_expert_1_answer":{"processed":"<p>I have defined race as a worldview and as an ideology of human differences predicated on the assumption of a natural inequality among human groups. \"Racism\" is any action or behavior that reflects this worldview.</p>"},"field_expert_2":{"processed":"James Horton"},"field_expert_3_name":{"processed":"Audrey Smedley"},"field_expert_4_name":null,"field_expert_4_answer":null}},"pageContext":{"jsonName":"qa-is-there-a-distinction-between-race-and-racism-57d","internalComponentName":"ComponentQaIsThereADistinctionBetweenRaceAndRacism","path":"/qa/is-there-a-distinction-between-race-and-racism","component":"/Users/eugene/Desktop/Race2/src/templates/qa.js","componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-qa-js","context":{"id":"13c0dc83-2779-4745-a976-911cb156db36"},"updatedAt":1531332572319,"pluginCreator___NODE":"Plugin default-site-plugin","pluginCreatorId":"Plugin default-site-plugin","componentPath":"/Users/eugene/Desktop/Race2/src/templates/qa.js","id":"13c0dc83-2779-4745-a976-911cb156db36"}}